00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:45,400
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Get out of the way!

276
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:00,330
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You!

277
00:30:04,010 --> 00:30:07,260
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well done, Rolfe, bringing back a heathen as an example.

278
00:30:07,430 --> 00:30:10,640
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at her. She sticks out like a sore thumb.

279
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:13,390
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas is here as an emissary of her people.

280
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:14,930
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A personal guest of the king.

281
00:30:15,100 --> 00:30:17,890
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The king has appointed me to lead an armada against the savages.

282
00:30:18,060 --> 00:30:22,310
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't tell me you didn't know? The king wants his gold.

283
00:30:22,980 --> 00:30:26,440
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- There is no gold.  - Another barbarian lie.

284
00:30:26,610 --> 00:30:30,410
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As soon as the ships are armed, I set sail to destroy the heathens

285
00:30:30,570 --> 00:30:33,410
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and reclaim Jamestown for James.

286
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:41,500
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We must stop him! Warn your king of his lies!

287
00:30:41,670 --> 00:30:45,670
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But he wasn't lying. The parchment bore the king's seal.

288
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:50,260
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What? Then your king's promise to meet me was the lie.

289
00:30:50,430 --> 00:30:54,100
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- The king doesn't lie!  - They cannot both be true.

290
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:58,100
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. It's just a misunderstanding. It has to be.

291
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:02,520
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can straighten this out. Come on.

292
00:31:11,110 --> 00:31:13,070
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you riding or running?

293
00:31:33,550 --> 00:31:34,800
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mrs.Jenkins!

294
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:41,810
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gods be gracious, is that my Johnny?

295
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:53,280
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Johnny, you need a bath.

296
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:56,530
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Johnny!  - Look at you.

297
00:31:59,410 --> 00:32:01,410
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, you.

298
00:32:02,290 --> 00:32:05,420
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mrs.Jenkins, I would like to introduce Pocahontas.

299
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,290
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, Mrs.Jenkins.

300
00:32:07,460 --> 00:32:09,760
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Jenkins have been with the Rolfes for generations.

301
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:13,680
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Careful. She's about to put on tea.  - I'll put on some tea.

302
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,680
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, and Uttamatomakkin.

303
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:24,600
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll put on lots and lots of tea.

304
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:28,860
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I'm off to see the king.  - I want to go with you.

305
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:33,360
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, the conventions in England are very complex.

306
00:32:33,530 --> 00:32:36,620
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I must go alone.  - But...

307
00:32:36,780 --> 00:32:38,870
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I promise, I will arrange for you to see the king.

308
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,700
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My word as a gentleman. Trust me.

309
00:33:15,610 --> 00:33:19,320
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I must find a way to warn my people, to stop this.

310
00:33:19,490 --> 00:33:21,660
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave it to Johnny.

311
00:33:21,830 --> 00:33:25,540
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He gave you his word as a gentleman, my dear.

312
00:33:25,710 --> 00:33:28,000
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can stake your life on that.

313
00:33:28,330 --> 00:33:31,460
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't exactly bring the Indian chief.

314
00:33:32,340 --> 00:33:36,510
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, no, no, no. I told you I would meet with the chief and no one less.

315
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:39,260
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Knight to bishop three.

316
00:33:40,220 --> 00:33:43,430
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sire, I gave these people your word you would meet.

317
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:47,100
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Are we not honour-bound...  - The king is bound to nothing,

318
00:33:47,270 --> 00:33:49,060
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}when you can not fulfil your mission.

319
00:33:49,230 --> 00:33:53,030
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You were sent for the savage leader, and yet you bring back a woman.

320
00:33:53,190 --> 00:33:54,230
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A woman!

321
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,650
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your Highness, she is royalty, a princess.

322
00:33:57,820 --> 00:34:00,030
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She is the daughter of a great chief

323
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:03,540
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}who has travelled far from her homeland in the interests of peace.

324
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:05,750
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Meet with her, Your Majesty.

325
00:34:06,370 --> 00:34:08,670
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}May I suggest she attend the Hunt Ball?

326
00:34:08,830 --> 00:34:12,000
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let her go back to Virginia having witnessed the royal might

327
00:34:12,170 --> 00:34:15,300
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and majesty of English society.

328
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:18,050
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sire, she doesn't know our customs.

329
00:34:18,220 --> 00:34:20,180
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}To subject her to this kind of scrutiny would be...

330
00:34:20,340 --> 00:34:22,430
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, I don't understand, Rolfe.

331
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:25,970
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If she's not a savage, then why shouldn't she fit in?

332
00:34:26,140 --> 00:34:28,310
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excellent idea, Ratcliffe.

333
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:31,650
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Rolfe, you will bring her to the Hunt Ball.

334
00:34:31,810 --> 00:34:34,780
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Prove to me she is as civilised as you claim,

335
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:37,570
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and I will stop my armada.

336
00:34:37,740 --> 00:34:40,360
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- If not, the armada sails.  - But, sire...

337
00:34:40,530 --> 00:34:43,990
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- It is decided!  - Pawn to king!

338
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:47,290
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Check.

339
00:34:51,330 --> 00:34:53,880
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- How did it go?  - A disaster.

340
00:34:54,050 --> 00:34:56,550
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's invited to the Hunt Ball!

341
00:34:56,710 --> 00:34:59,260
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Flabberdy-jacks.

342
00:35:08,180 --> 00:35:10,980
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You were successful? When do I see the king?

343
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:13,650
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Our meeting with the king has been corrupted.

344
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:16,900
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You're now invited to the Hunt Ball.  - I don't understand.

345
00:35:17,070 --> 00:35:20,900
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, it's a trap! Ratcliffe manipulated the king!

346
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:23,990
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's saying that if you're civilised you can fit right in.

347
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:27,990
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But it's the elite of British society, etiquette and manners.

348
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:31,410
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's a million ways you can insult someone. Believe me, I know.

349
00:35:31,580 --> 00:35:33,130
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And if you slip up just once,

350
00:35:33,290 --> 00:35:37,000
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Ratcliffe can convince the king...  - Then I must not slip up.

351
00:35:37,590 --> 00:35:39,800
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can't learn your ways alone,

352
00:35:39,970 --> 00:35:42,340
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but you can help me.

353
00:35:42,510 --> 00:35:44,010
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What must I do?

354
00:36:03,820 --> 00:36:05,530
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}John Rolfe!

355
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:09,200
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How do I look?

356
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:13,540
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lovely, in your... underwear.

357
00:36:13,710 --> 00:36:17,540
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Didn't Mrs.Jenkins...? Mrs.Jenkins!

358
00:36:20,050 --> 00:36:22,970
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my dear! Oh, come along, now.

359
00:36:23,130 --> 00:36:25,300
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's go finish your dressing.

360
00:36:40,230 --> 00:36:43,650
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Have no fear We're all right #

361
00:36:43,820 --> 00:36:47,450
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You've got me, dear to see you're a lady tonight #

362
00:36:47,620 --> 00:36:50,700
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# What seems strange is just new #

363
00:36:50,870 --> 00:36:54,920
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# People change every day till they find their own way #

364
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:57,750
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# So can you #

365
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:02,050
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And wait till he sees you after you're dressed #

366
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:05,720
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# I think the king will be very impressed #

367
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:09,390
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Wait till he sees you walking with ease #

368
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:12,970
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# He'll be so pleased you came down from the trees #

369
00:37:13,140 --> 00:37:16,100
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You'll be fine I can tell #

370
00:37:16,270 --> 00:37:19,980
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# It's a very good sign that you're doing so well #

371
00:37:20,150 --> 00:37:22,980
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# One more tuck One more bow #

372
00:37:23,150 --> 00:37:25,650
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Don't get stuck on that clasp #

373
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:29,570
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Johnny's lucky they asked you to go #

374
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:34,660
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# 'Cause wait till he sees you He'll be so proud #

375
00:37:34,830 --> 00:37:38,330
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Maybe he'll smile if he thinks he's allowed #

376
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:42,250
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Wait till he sees you there in your curls #

377
00:37:42,420 --> 00:37:46,380
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# John's always had such a fondness for girls #

378
00:37:46,550 --> 00:37:47,930
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# With curls #

379
00:37:48,090 --> 00:37:50,140
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And wait #

380
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:53,100
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Wait till you're out on the floor #

381
00:37:53,810 --> 00:37:57,390
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Show them what dancing is for #

382
00:37:57,560 --> 00:38:01,150
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Music is all you need See where a dance can lead #

383
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:03,280
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You two might come to see #

384
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:08,200
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You were meant to be so much more #

385
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:11,830
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Wait till he sees you Wait till tonight #

386
00:38:11,990 --> 00:38:15,410
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Fate has a way of arranging what's right #

387
00:38:15,580 --> 00:38:18,920
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# After he sees you in your new clothes #

388
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:22,750
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# A lady of grace from your head to your toes #

389
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:26,170
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Pretty and pink as the roses he grows #

390
00:38:26,340 --> 00:38:29,220
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Who knows Who knows #

391
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:31,180
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# I can't wait! #

392
00:38:33,890 --> 00:38:36,390
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, I've got something for you.

393
00:38:46,610 --> 00:38:48,030
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Flit, stop it!

394
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:51,700
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It doesn't belong here any more.

395
00:39:01,250 --> 00:39:03,210
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's beautiful!

396
00:39:35,410 --> 00:39:39,500
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have personally taken charge of the entertainment for the Hunt Ball.

397
00:39:39,660 --> 00:39:44,750
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I want to make sure nothing goes... right.

398
00:39:47,710 --> 00:39:50,090
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, how do I look? Pretty good?

399
00:39:51,260 --> 00:39:53,470
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Say, I thought you were getting dressed.

400
00:39:56,010 --> 00:39:57,720
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're right. You look great.

401
00:39:57,890 --> 00:40:00,480
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just don't talk so much tonight and we'll be fine.

402
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:24,830
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's called powder.

403
00:40:27,090 --> 00:40:29,380
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You look beautiful.

404
00:40:45,650 --> 00:40:47,230
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll put on some tea.

405
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:06,080
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Duke of Edinburgh.

406
00:41:06,500 --> 00:41:08,210
{\fnCambria\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lady Gray.

